<li><b>On the <i>Molk</i> sacrifice</b>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.humnet.ucla.edu/humnet/nelc/stelasite/report.html" class="external text" title="http://www.humnet.ucla.edu/humnet/nelc/stelasite/report.html" rel="nofollow">A Preliminary Report on the Incirli Stele</a> (Discussion of a stele with Phoenician text which may equate <i>molk</i>/<i>mulk</i> to first-born son).</li>
<li><a href="http://almashriq.hiof.no/ddc/projects/archaeology/berytus-back/berytus39/seeden-tophet/" class="external text" title="http://almashriq.hiof.no/ddc/projects/archaeology/berytus-back/berytus39/seeden-tophet/" rel="nofollow">HelgaSeeden, "A tophet in Tyre?" 1991.</a> from <i>Bertyus</i> 39 (American University of Beirut).</li>
<li><a href="http://www.xenos.org/classes/papers/aneidola.htm#Note11" class="external text" title="http://www.xenos.org/classes/papers/aneidola.htm#Note11" rel="nofollow">Amman excavation</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>


